ODM leaders have told the National Council of Churches to stop playing tribal politics.The group on Thursday asked NASA flagbearer Raila Odinga to assure Kenyans he will accept the election outcome.Secretary general Canon Karanja urged Raila to follow President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s lead. Uhuru has announced he will hand over power if defeated on August 8. But ODM said Karanja&rsquo;s statement is preemptive. Chairman John Mbadi on Thursday asked why the NCCK wants Raila to accept results of an election that is yet to be held.He accused the NCCK officials of engaging in tribal politics. Mbadi said the opposition will not accept the results of a rigged election.&ldquo;The consequences of poll rigging will be dire. We are going to win the election. How can we accept defeat in an election we are going to win?&rdquo; Mbadi askedHe was speaking in Nyando, Kisumu county. &ldquo;Let the church address the IEBC to ensure it conducts a free and fair election,&rdquo; the Suba South MP said. Ugunja MP Opiyo Wandayi said Kenyans cannot be coerced to accept results of a flawed election.He said it is the IEBC&rsquo;s job to conduct elections, not ODM&rsquo;s. Kisumu Senator Anyang&rsquo; Nyong&rsquo;o called for the abolition of an imperial presidency. He said an opinion poll by the National Intelligence Service put NASA ahead with 58 per cent, Jubilee at 42 per cent. This has not been disclosed.